bug.short_desc: Can't read Firefox tooltip text (white font on yellow background)
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1170708 Screenshot
Description of problem: Firefox on F24 Cinnamon uses white font on yellow background, what is almost unreadable. Thunderbird instead uses black on yellow. Please change this in Firefox.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): firefox-47.0-4.fc24.x86_64
How reproducible: Always.
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Open Firefox 2. Move the cursor over a menu item or something on the web page that shows up a tooltip text.
Actual results: Tooltip uses white font on yellow background. See attached screenshot.
Expected results: Tooltip should use a colour combination, that allows to read the text (e. g. black on yellow, like Thunderbird does).
